    "created_at": "2016-08-07T17:35:05Z",
    "updated_at": "2016-08-07T17:35:05Z",
    "body": "I've got most of it working now, but still need to handle file links (which can be used to create a custom Recent/Frequent list of files). The API has changed a little from my initial proposal to allow developers to properly deal with users removing items from custom categories, so it now looks like this:\n\n```\napp.setJumpList(\n  (minSlots, removedItems) => [\n    { category: 'Category 1', type: 'custom', items: [\n      { type: 'task', title: 'Task A', program: ... },\n      { type: 'task', title: 'Task B', program: ... },\n    ]},\n    { category: 'Category 2', items: [\n      { type: 'task', title: 'Task C', program: ... }\n    ]},\n    // Custom recently opened file list\n    { category: 'Recent',, items: [\n      { type: 'file', path: ... },\n      { type: 'file', path: ... }\n    ]},\n    // OS managed frequently opened file list\n    { type: 'frequent' },\n    // standard \"Tasks\" category, may contain separators\n    { items: [\n      { type: 'task', title: 'Task D', program: ... },\n      { type: 'separator' },\n      { type: 'task', title: 'Task D', program: ... }\n    ]},\n  ]\n)\n```\n\nCurrent work is over at https://github.com/enlight/electron/tree/win-setjumplist\n\n@bnookala I'll rewrite `app.setUserTasks` to just call `app.setJumpList` under the covers, can deprecate it later perhaps.\n"
  },
